&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mob Entertainment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is a startup multimedia studio that is best known for our hit indie horror game &quot;&lt;strong&gt;Poppy Playtime&quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp; This franchise is one of the hottest new properties in gaming, and our team is naturally expanding as our ambition expands.&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;To give a taste of our brand&#39;s popularity, more than 100 billion YouTube views of Poppy Playtime related content have occurred since the game&#39;s launch 4 years ago.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mob Entertainment is seeking an experienced and highly organized Brand Assurance Lead to oversee the development of consumer products from initial concept through launch. This role serves as a key liaison between internal stakeholders, creative teams, and external partners, whether licensing partners or direct-to-consumer vendors to ensure products are developed on time, on brand, and to the highest quality standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is passionate about consumer products, understands the complexities of product development across both licensed and direct-to-consumer channels, and thrives in a fast-paced environment managing multiple categories and partners simultaneously.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Development &amp;amp; Approval Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage product development across multiple categories and channels, from concept through launch, including both licensed and direct-to-consumer product lines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and approve product concepts, artwork, packaging, prototypes, and production samples to ensure brand consistency and quality standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide creative and technical feedback to partners and vendors throughout the development process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all products accurately reflect brand guidelines, character integrity, and franchise storytelling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor marketplace trends, competitor activity, and category innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide recommendations for product assortment, packaging, and merchandising opportunities.&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner &amp;amp; Vendor Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the day-to-day product development contact for assigned partners, licensees, and/or direct-to-consumer vendors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct regular status meetings with partners to track milestones, resolve challenges, and ensure timely execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide partners through the product approval process and communicate brand expectations clearly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong relationships with partners to drive successful product launches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Licensing, Marketing, Creative, and Game Development teams to align product development with company objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate the delivery of style guides, assets, reference materials, and creative direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate internal reviews and approvals with key stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track product development timelines and key milestones from concept to retail launch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain development calendars and approval schedules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify risks, delays, or quality concerns and proactively develop solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure products are delivered within agreed launch windows and retail timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&

