&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Mob Entertainment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mob Entertainment is the independent studio behind &lt;strong&gt;Poppy Playtime&lt;/strong&gt;, one of the world&#39;s most recognizable horror game franchises. We create memorable worlds filled with atmosphere, mystery, and environmental storytelling that captivate millions of players across PC and console.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Contract Environment Prop Artist&lt;/strong&gt; to join our Environment Art team and help bring our worlds to life. This role is ideal for an artist who enjoys building high-quality game-ready props, thrives in a collaborative environment, and can quickly contribute to an established visual style.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Contract Environment Prop Artist&lt;/strong&gt;, you will work closely with the Environment Art team to create and polish a wide variety of environmental props that support gameplay, storytelling, and world building. You&#39;ll help produce assets that fit seamlessly into our levels while maintaining high artistic and technical quality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll collaborate daily with Material Artists, Level Designers, Technical Artists, and Art Leadership to deliver optimized assets that meet production goals and performance requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a contract position and requires someone who can quickly integrate into an existing production pipeline and deliver consistently high-quality work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create high-quality, game-ready environmental props from concept through final implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, UV, and prepare high-quality environmental assets using mid poly, trim sheet and floater workflows.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce assets that match Mob Entertainment&#39;s artistic style and visual quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize assets for performance while maintaining visual fidelity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work from concept art, photo reference, design documentation, or existing style guides.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with ELevel Designers to support level production and asset needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement assets into Unreal Engine and perform basic scene setup as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in art reviews and respond constructively to feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain organized source files and follow naming conventions and pipeline standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with asset polish and support environment production during milestone delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate progress proactively and identify potential production risks early.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
