&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mob Entertainment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is a startup multimedia studio that is best known for our hit indie horror game &quot;&lt;strong&gt;Poppy Playtime&quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp; This franchise is one of the hottest new properties in gaming, and our team is naturally expanding as our ambition expands.&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;To give a taste of our brand&#39;s popularity, more than 100 billion YouTube views of Poppy Playtime related content have occurred since the game&#39;s launch 4 years ago.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Mob Entertainment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mob Entertainment is the indie studio behind the hit animated horror franchise &lt;em&gt;Poppy Playtime&lt;/em&gt;, known for its dark, creature-driven storytelling and visually immersive world-building. As we expand into animated content and cinematic experiences, we&#39;re looking for skilled storytellers to help bring our vision to the screen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Position&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Summary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced Senior Previsualization Artist to spearhead the visualization of cinematic storytelling, action sequences, and key creative moments throughout production. This role serves as a critical bridge between creative vision and execution, partnering closely with creative leadership, designers, artists, and production teams to develop compelling visual narratives before production begins.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate combines exceptional storytelling instincts with advanced 3D visualization skills and a deep understanding of cinematography, editing, and shot design. They are capable of independently driving complex sequences from concept through final previs while mentoring others and helping establish visualization best practices across projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create high-quality previsualization sequences that communicate story, performance, pacing, camera language, and cinematic intent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate scripts, story treatments, creative briefs, and stakeholder feedback into clear and compelling visual sequences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive shot design, camera blocking, and visual storytelling decisions for complex cinematic and action-driven sequences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with directors, creative leadership, production, design, animation, and art teams to align previs work with project goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and assemble environments, cameras, characters, and action sequences using 3D tools and real-time engines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create storyboards, animatics, and previs presentations to support creative reviews and production planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify storytelling, technical, and production challenges early and propose effective visual solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain previs workflows, standards, and best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide guidance, feedback, and mentorship to junior artists and external partners when applicable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present work to stakeholders and effectively communicate creative rationale behind visual decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support cinematic, marketing, gameplay, and transmedia initiatives as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
